$interpreted: Aosta: ...That's about it. Hmm?
Shop Owner: Mister, that's quite a lot of stuff you're buying. Do you have an assistant to help you carry them?
Aosta: No...I want this one as well.
Shop Owner: What? I'm sorry, but that book was already reserved by someone else.
Aosta: Who?
Ralph: Me. That book is about the history and legends of the Feather Clan. I imagine that you're interested as well?
Ralph: Huh? Professor Clovis? It's been a long time.
Aosta: Who are you?
Ralph: Umm...I'm Ralph Lavande. I took several of your classes before at Rune Academy.
Aosta: Doesn't ring any bells.
Ralph: Wait, if you're studying the Feather Clan as well, how about we work together?
Aosta: What do you mean?
Ralph: To be honest, I got my hands on some classified documents. However, I may not be able to unravel the mysteries contained within on my own.
Ralph: So, do you want to help me?
Aosta: Are you feeling me out?
Ralph: No. What I'm thinking is that I'll provide you with the documents, but in return, I would like you to share your research with me.
Aosta: Sounds worth a try. Do you want to be my assistant?
Aosta: If you don't want to, then forget it.
Ralph: L-Let me try...no, I want to try!
Aosta: Good. Follow me.
Ralph: So this is your laboratory? What's the deal with the monsters wandering near the door?
Aosta: Probably drawn in by the research materials. Hmm, since the monsters are already here, let's use them to see what you got.
Ralph: Whew~ Isn't this a hassle? Why don't you just set up a monster insulation device?
Aosta: Good point. I'll consider it.
